        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Just to add to my post cause Syrox brought up another point.</P><P>My understanding about specialization is that you can have one skill increase beyond 50 but all your casting skills can have specialization of 50...which I would assume is a specialization check 5% of the time...whereas with one skill you get roughly a 25% chance to make the specialization skill check without Spell Casting Mastery.  The spell casting mastery does not say your specialization for only one skill gets increased.  Your specialization check gets increased...meaning increased chance for ALL your specialization checks.  So with SCM level 3, you will have a 35% of making the specialization roll on ANY spell you cast and a 55% chance of making the specialization roll on your primary specialization(mine being Alteration).  THAT is why I feel SCM is the FIRST choice for ARCH skill.  You will save soooooooo much manna with this skill.  That is why I think SCM3 is UberIshious.</P><P>Just wanted to clarify my position.</P><P>Ish Out</P><P></P><P>Edited by - ishtarra on 12/19/2001  09:05:57</font></td>
